		<hr size="1">I am Finally a Lv 20 SK Ogre on the Rathe Server.  As with most good SK players, (in my opinion anyway), im so sick of hearing the whining about how bad the SK class is.  What are you whiners talking about?  A weak pet?  What, you think its gonna tank while you stand back and cast disease cloud??  Pull, tank, taunt, and watch ur little bone rack buddy throw in up to 20 damage per round.  Key is to keep the baddie off of him, using taunt.  Also, the pet is a HUGE help when fighting casters, so how is that useless?  Next, at Lv 15, Clinging Darkness is awesome.  Use it to pull, then drill the baddie with arrows from a good bow until it gets to you, then tank.  Usually when fighting in an open area, I can hit the target for 14 to 60 damage before it gets to me, depending on the situation of course.  How many times has Fear saved a party member?  How many times has Shadow Step saved me??  ALOT.  Now for the melee part of it.  Up to Lv 20 my melee was OK, not great.  At 20 I now slash for 40 - 53 damage with my BIBS.  Plus now I have double attack so, so I slash for that damage twice per round.  I group fight mostly in fast spawn locations like HH and cazic, so I have been leveling VERY fast.  The ONLY two problems I have with my OGRE SK, is his slow regen when fighting alone.  My bind wound is great but it only gets me back to 50% life, and the sit for the other 300 hit points is sometimes hateful.  If I had know better when I started I would have been a Troll, but too late now.  Second, when my HT is resisted when I am DEPENDING on it, I get a little pissed, but HOPEFULLY this will be taken care of.  Other then that, why dont the whiners just change classes, do whatever it takes to make you happy, just PLEASE stop whining about the SK class.  Thanks.  TUKUK<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
